body:
When running the `iverilog` command on this program: 
```systemverilog
module module_0 (
    id_2,
    id_3,
    id_18,
);
  inout id_18;
  input id_3;
  inout id_2;
  assign id_18 = id_3.id_2;
endmodule
``` 
iverilog crashes with the following output:

`
assert: elab_expr.cc:4964: failed assertion sr.path_tail.empty()
Aborted
`

code_blocks:
module module_0 (
